Blocking Queue:


Blocking Queue = Thread-safe queue where producers wait when full and consumers wait when empty,
avoiding busy waiting and enabling efficient producer-consumer communication.


A thread-safe queue where:

Producer waits if queue is full.
Consumer waits if queue is empty.

Used in Producer-Consumer pattern.


Producer ---> Blocking Queue ---> Consumer



Why do we need it?

Without a blocking queue:

Consumer
   │
   ▼
while(true) {
   if(queue not empty)
      consume();
}

This wastes CPU (busy waiting).



With a blocking queue:

Consumer
   │
take()
   │
(waiting)
   │
Message arrives
   ▼
consume

Thread sleeps efficiently until data arrives.




