Thread Pool



Creating and destroying threads is expensive because it involves OS-level operations.

Instead of creating a new thread for every request, we pre-create a fixed number of worker threads and keep them ready in a pool.

           Task Queue
                │
     ┌──────────┼──────────┐
     ▼          ▼          ▼
 Thread1    Thread2    Thread3
 (idle)     (idle)     (idle)




When a task arrives:

Task arrives
    │
    ▼
Task Queue
    │
    ▼
Available Thread picks task
    │
    ▼
Executes task





When finished:

Thread completes task
      │
      ▼
Returns to pool
      │
      ▼
Waits for next task



