Service Discovery 


In a microservices architecture:

User Service → Order Service → Payment Service

Each service may have multiple instances:

Order Service
 ├─ Instance 1
 ├─ Instance 2
 └─ Instance 3

IPs keep changing because:

Auto-scaling
Container restarts
Deployments
Failures

Hardcoding IPs won't work.

Service Discovery

A central registry maintains information about all service instances.



               Service Registry
              (Eureka/Zookeeper/Consul)
                     ▲
                     │
       Register      │      Lookup
                     │
                     ▼
Service A  <------>  Service B




Service Lookup

Suppose User Service wants Order Service.

User Service
      │
      ▼
Ask Registry:
"Where is order-service?"
      │
      ▼
[IP1, IP2, IP3]

Then User Service picks one instance (often using load balancing).



